dasanAdslMIB.name: dasanAdslMIB
dasanAdslMIB.description: The MIB module to describe ADSL product. The MIB module that provides objects that are proprietary and extension to ADSL- LINE-MIB. The MIB include extension to following Tables. 1.) adslLineTable 2.) adslAtucPhysTable 3.) adslAturPhysTable 4.) adslAtucChanTable 5.) adslAturChanTable 6.) adslAtucPerfDataTable --7.) adslAturPerfDataTable 8.) adslAtucIntervalTable --9.) adslAturIntervalTable 10.) adslAtucChanPerfDataTable 11.) adslAturChanPerfDataTable 12.) adslAtucChanIntervalTable 13.) adslAturChanIntervalTable 14.) adslLineConfProfileTable 15.) adslLineAlarmConfProfileTable The MIB also include a set of scalar(s) clubbed under the group 'dsAdslCapabilityGroup'.

dsDslSystemDslType.name: dsDslSystemDslType
dsDslSystemDslType.description: This object identifies the firmware to be downloaded.

dsDslSystemLineCodingType.name: dsDslSystemLineCodingType
dsDslSystemLineCodingType.description: This object indicates ADSL line code type.

dsDslSystemLineTxCfg.name: dsDslSystemLineTxCfg
dsDslSystemLineTxCfg.description: This object indicates transmission capabilities with which the DSL system is configured.

dsAdslCapabilityLineTxCap.name: dsAdslCapabilityLineTxCap
dsAdslCapabilityLineTxCap.description: This bitmap specifies which all transmission modes, which the ATU-C is capable of supporting. Right now support for Annex A (q9921PotsNonOverlapped(2) and q9921PotsOverlapped(3)) is present. This value depends on the DSL PHY firmware present on Columbia MND

dsAdslLineExtnTable.name: dsAdslLineExtnTable
dsAdslLineExtnTable.description: This table includes common attributes describing both ends of the line. It is required for all ADSL physical interfaces. This Table is an extension to adslLineTable defined in rfc-2662.

dsAdslLineExtnEntry.name: dsAdslLineExtnEntry
dsAdslLineExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslLineExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex.

dsAdslLineExtnAction.name: dsAdslLineExtnAction
dsAdslLineExtnAction.description: this object indicates parameter that allows actions on a per line basis. These actions include abort, startup, and tests.

dsAdslLineExtnUtopiaL2RxAddr.name: dsAdslLineExtnUtopiaL2RxAddr
dsAdslLineExtnUtopiaL2RxAddr.description: This object indicates UTOPIA Level 2 Rx address for a line.

dsAdslLineExtnUtopiaL2TxAddr.name: dsAdslLineExtnUtopiaL2TxAddr
dsAdslLineExtnUtopiaL2TxAddr.description: This object indicates UTOPIA Level 2 Tx address for a line.

dsAdslLineExtnTransAtucCap.name: dsAdslLineExtnTransAtucCap
dsAdslLineExtnTransAtucCap.description: The transmission modes that the ATU-C is capable of supporting. The modes available are limited by the design of the equipment. REFERENCE Section 7.3.2 ITU G.997.1.

dsAdslLineExtnTransAtucActual.name: dsAdslLineExtnTransAtucActual
dsAdslLineExtnTransAtucActual.description: The transmission mode of the ATU-C. This object returns if there is no mode currently known. The initialization with the ATU-R will determine the mode used. REFERENCE Section 7.3.2 ITU G.997.1.

dsAdslLineExtnClockType.name: dsAdslLineExtnClockType
dsAdslLineExtnClockType.description: This object indicates parameter to set use of either crystal or oscillator.

dsAdslLineExtnLineDmtTrellis.name: dsAdslLineExtnLineDmtTrellis
dsAdslLineExtnLineDmtTrellis.description: Parameter that indicates whether trellis coding has been enabled or disabled. Trellis coding should always be enabled for its clear performance advantage.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTable.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTable
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC. This table is an extention to adslAtucPhysTable defined in rfc-2662.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnEntry
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnOpState.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnOpState
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnOpState.description: This object indicates the operational state of the ATU. Values include idle,handshake, training, etc.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnActualStd.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnActualStd
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnActualStd.description: This object provides actual ATU-C configuration based on outcome of negotiation with ATU-R. In this case, the parameter provides actual standard used for the connection.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnBertError.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnBertError
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnBertError.description: This object indicates the No. of bit errors detected during BERT.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTxAtmCellCounter.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTxAtmCellCounter
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTxAtmCellCounter.description: This object Provides transmit ATM cell counter.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnRxAtmCellCounter.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnRxAtmCellCounter
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnRxAtmCellCounter.description: This object Provides receive ATM cell counter.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnStartProgress.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnStartProgress
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnStartProgress.description: This object provides current detailed start up information to be used for debugging.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnBertSync.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnBertSync
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnBertSync.description: Indicates if the Signal is in Sync or not.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnParametricTestResult.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnParametricTestResult
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnParametricTestResult.description: Indicates the Result of the Parametric Test conducted on the Xcvr.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDataBoostStatus.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDataBoostStatus
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDataBoostStatus.description: This object indicates whether DataBoost is utilized for the connection.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTestArray.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTestArray
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnTestArray.description: This object indicates the Parametric Test Array. Every Four octects refer to one element in this array of octets.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChanPerfCD.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChanPerfCD
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChanPerfCD.description: The near-end delineated total cell count performance parameter is a count of the total number of cells passed through the cell delineation and HEC function process operating on the ATM Data Path while in the SYNC state. (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChanPerfBE.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChanPerfBE
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChanPerfBE.description: The near-end idle bit error count performance parameter is a count of the number of bit errors in the idle cell payload received in the ATM Data Path at the near-end. (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLINSCus.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLINSCus
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLINSCus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the scale factor to be applied to the upstream Hlin(f) values.(Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus).

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLINpsus.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLINpsus
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLINpsus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of complex upstream Hlin(f) values in linear scale. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus). Every two octets refer to one element in this array of octets.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLOGMTus.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLOGMTus
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLOGMTus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the upstream Hlog(f).(Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus).

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLOGpsus.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLOGpsus
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltHLOGpsus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real upstream Hlog(f) values in dB. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus). Every two octets refer to one element in this array of octets.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltQLNMTus.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltQLNMTus
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltQLNMTus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the upstream QLN(f) values. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus).

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltQLNpsus.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltQLNpsus
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltQLNpsus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real upstream QLN(f) values in dB. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus). Every two octets refer to one element in this array of octets.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltLastTxState.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltLastTxState
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnDeltLastTxState.description: DELT-related parameter that provides last successful transmitted initialization state by the ATU-C. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus).

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnPMState.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnPMState
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnPMState.description: Line Power Management State. (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChanPerfCU.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChanPerfCU
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChanPerfCU.description: The near-end user total cell count performance parameter is a count of the total number of cells in the ATM Data Path delivered at the V-C (for ATU-C) or T-R (for ATU-R) interface. (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnExtendedPsdStatus.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnExtendedPsdStatus
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnExtendedPsdStatus.description: GlobespanVirata parameter that indicates whether an extended or the standard upstream PSD is used - for G.Span Plus mode of operation only. Only supported for G.Span Plus, therefore this parameter is not valid for ADSL2/ADSL2plus modes of operation.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChipVersion.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChipVersion
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnChipVersion.description: GlobespanVirata parameter that indicates the DSP version number.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnPilotTone.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnPilotTone
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnPilotTone.description: GlobespanVirata parameter that indicates the Pilot Tone Index.

dsAdslAtucMSGds.name: dsAdslAtucMSGds
dsAdslAtucMSGds.description: Indicates the Overhead Channel. This feature is not supported by DSLPHY as yet.

dsAdslAtucPhysExtnPsdMaskMode.name: dsAdslAtucPhysExtnPsdMaskMode
dsAdslAtucPhysExtnPsdMaskMode.description: GlobespanVirata parameter that indicates the actual Psd Mask currently being used.

dsAdslAturPhysExtnTable.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnTable
dsAdslAturPhysExtnTable.description: This table is an extention to adslAtucPhysTable defined in rfc-2662. This table provides one row for each ATUR. Each row contains the Physical Layer Parameters table for that ATUR.

dsAdslAturPhysExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnEntry
dsAdslAturPhysExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAturPhysExtnTable. The Table is indexed by IfIndex.

dsAdslAturPhysExtnConfig.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnConfig
dsAdslAturPhysExtnConfig.description: This object provides the upstream and downstream ATU-R configuration data (EOC - read 5 sec after data mode).

dsAdslAturPhysExtnChanPerfCD.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnChanPerfCD
dsAdslAturPhysExtnChanPerfCD.description: The far-end delineated total cell count performance parameter is a count of the total number of cells passed through the cell delineation and HEC function process operating on the ATM Data Path while in the SYNC state.(Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAturPhysExtnChanPerfCU.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnChanPerfCU
dsAdslAturPhysExtnChanPerfCU.description: The far-end user total cell count performance parameter is a count of the total number of cells in the ATM Data Path delivered at the V-C (for ATU-C) or T-R (for ATUR) interface. (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAturPhysExtnChanPerfBE.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnChanPerfBE
dsAdslAturPhysExtnChanPerfBE.description: The far-end idle bit error count performance parameter is a count of the number of bit errors in the idle cell payload received in the ATM Data Path at the far-end. (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLINSCds.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLINSCds
dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLINSCds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the scale factor to be applied to the downstream Hlin(f) values.(Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus).

dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLINpsds.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLINpsds
dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLINpsds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of complex downstream Hlin(f) values in linear scale. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus). Every two octects refer to one element in this array of octets.

dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLOGMTds.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLOGMTds
dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLOGMTds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the downstream Hlog(f). (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus).

dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLOGpsus.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLOGpsus
dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltHLOGpsus.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real downstream Hlog(f) values in dB. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus).

dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltQLNMTds.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltQLNMTds
dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltQLNMTds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides the number of symbols used to measure the downstream QLN(f) values. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus).

dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltQLNpsds.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltQLNpsds
dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltQLNpsds.description: DELT-related parameter that provides an array of real downstream QLN(f) values in dB. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus). Every two octects refer to one element in this array of octets.

dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltLastTxState.name: dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltLastTxState
dsAdslAturPhysExtnDeltLastTxState.description: DELT-related parameter that provides last successful transmitted initialization state by the ATU-R. (Not available for ADSL and ADSL2plus).

dsAdslAturMSGus.name: dsAdslAturMSGus
dsAdslAturMSGus.description: Indicates the Overhead Channel. This feature is not supported by DSLPHY as yet.

dsAdslAtucChanExtnTable.name: dsAdslAtucChanExtnTable
dsAdslAtucChanExtnTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC channel. This Table is an extention to adslAtucChanTable defined in rfc 2662.

dsAdslAtucChanExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAtucChanExtnEntry
dsAdslAtucChanExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAtucChanExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex.

dsAdslAtucChanExtnCurrAtmStatus.name: dsAdslAtucChanExtnCurrAtmStatus
dsAdslAtucChanExtnCurrAtmStatus.description: indicates an ncd or lcd failure if the counter surpasses 127. If neither ATM counter surpasses 127, the return value will be 'NoAtmDefect'.

dsAdslAtucChanExtnRsSymbols.name: dsAdslAtucChanExtnRsSymbols
dsAdslAtucChanExtnRsSymbols.description: Indicates number of DMT symbols per Reed-Solomon code word (S) in the downstream direction. Note that S is not restricted to interleaved mode only. Even in fast mode, S is a valid constant value and is equal to 1.

dsAdslAtucChanExtnRsDepth.name: dsAdslAtucChanExtnRsDepth
dsAdslAtucChanExtnRsDepth.description: Indicates interleaving depth (D) in the downstream direction. Note that D is not restricted to interleaved mode only. Even in fast mode, D is a valid constant value and is equal to 1.

dsAdslAtucChanExtnRsRedundancy.name: dsAdslAtucChanExtnRsRedundancy
dsAdslAtucChanExtnRsRedundancy.description: Indicates number of redundant bytes (R) per Reed-Solomon code in the downstream direction.

dsAdslAturChanExtnTable.name: dsAdslAturChanExtnTable
dsAdslAturChanExtnTable.description: This table is extention to adslAturChanTable defined in rfc-2662. This table provides one row for each ATUR channel. ADSL channel interfaces are those Interface Table entries where ifType is equal to adslInterleave(124) or adslFast(125).

dsAdslAturChanExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAturChanExtnEntry
dsAdslAturChanExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAturChanExtnTable. The Table is indexed by IfIndex.

dsAdslAturChanExtnCurrAtmStatus.name: dsAdslAturChanExtnCurrAtmStatus
dsAdslAturChanExtnCurrAtmStatus.description: This object indicates an ncd or lcd failure if the counter surpasses 127. If neither ATM counter surpasses 127, the return value will be NoAtmDefect.

dsAdslAturChanExtnRsSymbols.name: dsAdslAturChanExtnRsSymbols
dsAdslAturChanExtnRsSymbols.description: This object indicates number of DMT symbols per Reed- Solomon code word (S) in the upstream direction Note that S is not restricted to interleaved mode only. Even in fast mode, S is a valid constant value and is equal to 1.

dsAdslAturChanExtnRsDepth.name: dsAdslAturChanExtnRsDepth
dsAdslAturChanExtnRsDepth.description: This object indicates interleaving depth (D) in the upstream direction Note that D is not restricted to interleaved mode only. Even in fast mode, D is a valid constant value and is equal to 1.

dsAdslAturChanExtnRsRedundancy.name: dsAdslAturChanExtnRsRedundancy
dsAdslAturChanExtnRsRedundancy.description: This object indicates number of redundant bytes (R) per Reed-Solomon code in the upstream direction.

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnTable.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnTable
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC. This table is extention to adslAtucPerfDataTable defined in rfc-2662.

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnEntry
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex.

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatFastR.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatFastR
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatFastR.description: The value of this object indicates the count of fast retrains. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.1

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatFailedFastR.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatFailedFastR
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatFailedFastR.description: The value of this object indicates the count of failed fast retrains. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.2

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatSesL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatSesL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatSesL.description: The value of this object indicates the count of severely errored second line. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.7

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatUasL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatUasL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatUasL.description: The value of this object indicates the count of unavailable errored seconds. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.9

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFastR.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFastR
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFastR.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was fast retrains. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.1

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFailedFas.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFailedFastR
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFailedFas.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was failed fast retrains. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.2

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinSesL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinSesL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinSesL.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was severely errored seconds. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.7

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinUasL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinUasL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinUasL.description: Count of seconds in the current 15 minute interval when there was count for unavailable errored seconds. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.9

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFastR.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFastR
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFastR.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was fast retrains during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1Day TimeElapsed. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.1

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFailedFast.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFailedFastR
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFailedFast.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was failed fast retrains during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1Day TimeElapsed.REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.2

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DaySesL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DaySesL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DaySesL.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Severely Errored Seconds during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.7

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayUasL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayUasL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayUasL.description: Count of the number of seconds when there was Unavailable Errored Seconds during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1DayTimeElapsed. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.9

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFastR.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFastR
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFastR.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was fast retrains within the most recent previous 1 day period. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.1

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFailedFast.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFailedFastR
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFailedFast.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was failed fast retrains within the most recent previous 1 day period. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.4.15.2

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DaySesL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DaySesL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DaySesL.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was severely errored seconds within the most recent previous 1 day period. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.7

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayUasL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayUasL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayUasL.description: Count of seconds in the interval when there was unavailable errored seconds within the most recent previous 1 day period. REFERENCE ITU G.997.1 Section 7.2.1.1.9

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayTimeElapse.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayTimeElapsed
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayTimeElapse.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval in seconds.

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatFecsL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatFecsL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatFecsL.description: Count of 1-second intervals with one or more forward error correction (FEC) anomalies since agent reset (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFecsL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFecsL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFecsL.description: Count of 1-second intervals, in the current 15 minute interval, with one or more forward error correction (FEC) anomalies (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFecsL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFecsL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFecsL.description: NCount of 1-second intervals, during the current day as measured by adslAtucPerfCurr1Day-TimeElapsed, with one or moreforward error correction (FEC) anomalies (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFecsL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFecsL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFecsL.description: Count of 1-second intervals, within the most recent previous 1-day period, with one or more forward error correction (FEC) anomalies (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatLossL.name: dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatLossL
dsAdslAtucPerfDataExtnStatLossL.description: Count of 1-second intervals containing one or more loss of signal (LOS) defects (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnTable.name: dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnTable
dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATU-R. ADSL physical interfaces are those Interface Table Entries where ifType is equal to adsl(94). This table is an extn to 'adslAturPerfDataExtTable' which is part of ADSL-LINE-EXT-MIB (rfc 3440).

dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnEntry
dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex.

dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnStatFecsL.name: dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnStatFecsL
dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnStatFecsL.description: Count of 1-second intervals with one or more far end forward error correction (FFEC) anomalies since agent reset (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFecsL.name: dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFecsL
dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnCurr15MinFecsL.description: Count of 1-second intervals containing one or more far end loss of signal (LOS) defects (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFecsL.name: dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFecsL
dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnCurr1DayFecsL.description: Count of 1-second intervals, during the current day as measured by adslAturPerfCurr1Day-TimeElapsed, with one or more far end forward error correction (FFEC) anomalies (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFecsL.name: dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFecsL
dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnPrev1DayFecsL.description: Count of 1-second intervals, within the most recent previous 1-day period, with one or more far end forward error correction (FFEC) anomalies (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnStatLossL.name: dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnStatLossL
dsAdslAturPerfDataExtnStatLossL.description: Count of 1-second intervals containing one or more far end loss of signal (LOS) defects (Not available for ADSL).

dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnTable.name: dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnTable
dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC performance data collection interval. This Table is an extention to adslAtucIntervalTable defined in rfc 2662.

dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnEntry
dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex and adslAtucIntervalNumber.

dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnFastR.name: dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnFastR
dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnFastR.description: This variable indicates Count of seconds in the interval when there was Fast Retrains.

dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnFailedFastR.name: dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnFailedFastR
dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnFailedFastR.description: This variable indicates Count of seconds in the interval when there was Failed Fast Retrains.

dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnSesL.name: dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnSesL
dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnSesL.description: This variable indicates Count of seconds in the interval when there was severely errored seconds.

dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnUasL.name: dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnUasL
dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnUasL.description: This variable indicates Count of seconds in the interval when there was unavailable errored seconds.

dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnTimeElapsed.name: dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnTimeElapsed
dsAdslAtucIntervalExtnTimeElapsed.description: This variable indicates the total Elapsed time in this interval.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnTable.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnTable
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnTable.description: This table provides one row for each ATUC channel. This table is an extention to adslAtucChanPerfDataTable.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnEntry
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnTimeElapsed.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnTimeElapsed
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnTimeElapsed.description: Total elapsed seconds in this interval.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnNcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnNcd
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnNcd.description: Count of no cell delineation(ncd) on this channel.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnOcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnOcd
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnOcd.description: Count of out of cell delineation (ocd) on this channel.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnHec.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnHec
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnHec.description: Header error check counter(hec) on this channel.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinNcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinNcd
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinNcd.description: Count of no cell delineation(ncd) on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinOcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinOcd
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinOcd.description: Count of out of cell delineation (ocd) on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinHec.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinHec
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinHec.description: Header error check counter(hec) on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayNcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayNcd
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayNcd.description: Count of no cell delineation (ncd) on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayOcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayOcd
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayOcd.description: Count of out of cell delineation (ocd) on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayHec.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayHec
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayHec.description: Header error check counter (hec) on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayNcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayNcd
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayNcd.description: Count of no cell delineation (ncd) on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayOcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayOcd
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayOcd.description: Count of out of cell delineation (ocd) on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayHec.name: dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayHec
dsAdslAtucChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayHec.description: Header error check counter(hec) on this channel within the most recent previous 1-day period.

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnTable.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnTable
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnTable.description: This table is extention to adslAturChanPerfDataTable defined in rfc-2662. This table contains the Performance Data for that ATU-R channel (fast or interleaved).

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnEntry
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnTable. The Table is indexed by IfIndex.

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnNcd.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnNcd
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnNcd.description: Number of packets with no cell delineation(NCD) error on this channel.

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnHec.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnHec
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnHec.description: Number of packets with Header error check (HEC) error on this channel.

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinNcd.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinNcd
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinNcd.description: Number of packets with no cell delineation(NCD) error on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinHec.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinHec
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr15MinHec.description: Number of packets with Header error check (HEC) error on this channel within the current 15 minute time interval.

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayNcd.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayNcd
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayNcd.description: Number of packets with no cell delineation (NCD) error on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayHec.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayHec
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnCurr1DayHec.description: Number of packets with Header error check (HEC) error on this channel within the current 1 day time interval.

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayNcd.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayNcd
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayNcd.description: Number of packets with no cell delineation (NCD) error on this channel within the most recent previous period.

dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayHec.name: dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayHec
dsAdslAturChanPerfDataExtnPrev1DayHec.description: Number of packets with Header error check (HEC) error on this channel within the most recent previous period.

dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnTable.name: dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnTable
dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnTable.description: This table provides a row for each ATUC channel's performance data collection interval. This table is an extension to adslAtucChanIntervalTable defined in rfc 2662.

dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnEntry
dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnTable. The Table is indexed by ifIndex and adslAtucChanIntervalNumber.

dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnTimeElapsed.name: dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnTimeElapsed
dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnTimeElapsed.description: Total time elapsed (in seconds) in this interval.

dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnNcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnNcd
dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnNcd.description: Indicates count of no cell delineation on this channel for this interval.

dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnOcd.name: dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnOcd
dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnOcd.description: Indicates count of out cell delineation on this channel for this interval.

dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnHec.name: dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnHec
dsAdslAtucChanIntervalExtnHec.description: Indicates Header error check counter on this channel during this interval.

dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnTable.name: dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnTable
dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnTable.description: This table is extention to adslAturChanIntervalTable defined in rfc-2662. This table provides one row for each ATUR channel's performance data collection interval.

dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnEntry.name: dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnEntry
dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnTable. The Table is indexed by IfIndex and dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnNumber.

dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnNcd.name: dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnNcd
dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnNcd.description: Indicates count of no cell delineation on this channel for this interval.

dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnHec.name: dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnHec
dsAdslAturChanIntervalExtnHec.description: Indicates Header error check counter on this channel during this interval.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTable.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTable
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTable.description: This table contains information on the ADSL line configuration. This Table is an extension to adslLineConfProfileTable.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnEntry.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnEntry
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTable. The Table is indexed by adslLineConfProfileName.

dsAdslLineConfProfileName.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileName
dsAdslLineConfProfileName.description: This object is used by the line configuration table in order to identify a row of this table.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRsIntCorrection.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRsIntCorrectionUp
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRsIntCorrection.description: Sets the correction time for the upstream-interleaved buffer. RS can also be disabled. The Default Value for ADSL+ is 3.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnLineType.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnLineType
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnLineType.description: This object is used to configure the ADSL physical line mode.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTxEndBin.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTxEndBin
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTxEndBin.description: Highest bin number allowed for Tx signal. The Range & default for ADSL+ is 0x06 - 0x1ff and 0x1ff respectively.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTxStartBin.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTxStartBin
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTxStartBin.description: Lowest bin number allowed for Tx signal.The Range for ADSL+ is 0x06 - 0x1ff. The Default for Annex B is 0x40 respectively.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRxStartBin.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRxStartBin
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRxStartBin.description: Lowest bin number allowed for Rx signal. The Range for ADSL+ is 0x01 - 0x1ff. The default for Annex B is 0x01.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRxEndBin.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRxEndBin
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRxEndBin.description: Highest bin number allowed for Rx signal. The Range and default value for ADSL+ is 0x01 - 0x1ff and 0x1d respectively.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnStandard.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnStandard
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnStandard.description: Preferred standard compliance. Outcome is dependent upon standard support of the remote unit.GlobespanVirata High Speed ADSL DMT (ADSL+) applications only.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTxPowerAttenuat.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTxPowerAttenuation
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnTxPowerAttenuat.description: Specifies value of Tx power attenuation.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRsFastOvrhdDown.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRsFastOvrhdDown
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRsFastOvrhdDown.description: Sets the percentage overhead for the downstream-fast buffer.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnIntCorrectionDo.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnIntCorrectionDown
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnIntCorrectionDo.description: This parameter sets the correction time for the downstream interleaved buffer.RS can also be disabled.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRsFastOvrhdUp.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRsFastOvrhdUp
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnRsFastOvrhdUp.description: Sets the 4576014verhead for the upstream-fast buffer.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnAnnexType.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnAnnexType
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnAnnexType.description: This parameter is set as per annex compliance of the code release. GlobespanVirata High Speed ADSL DMT (ADSL+) applications only.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnMaxDCo.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnMaxDCo
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnMaxDCo.description: This object is used to indicate Maximum interleaving depth supported by the customer's hardware.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnAdvertisedCapab.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnAdvertisedCapabilities
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnAdvertisedCapab.description: Controls if the CO will attempt to startup using alternate standards if the CPE does not support ADSL+.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPsdMaskType.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPsdMaskType
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPsdMaskType.description: Selects the PSD mask option to be used.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnLineDmtConfMode.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnLineDmtConfMode
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnLineDmtConfMode.description: Selects if there is overlap or no overlap of bins.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnUpstreamPSD.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnUpstreamPSD
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnUpstreamPSD.description: This object sets the upstream PSD to be either extended or standard. Used for GSpan Plus only.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPMMode.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPMMode
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPMMode.description: PM-related parameter used by the ATU-C to set the allowed link states.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML0Time.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML0Time
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML0Time.description: PM configuration parameter, related to the L2 low power state. This parameter represents the minimum time (in seconds) between an exit from the L2 state and the next entry into the L2 state.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2Time.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2Time
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2Time.description: PM configuration parameter, related to the L2 low power state. This parameter represents the minimum time (in seconds) between an Entry into the L2 state and the first Power Trim in the L2 state and between two consecutive Power Trims in the L2 State.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2ATPR.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2ATPR
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2ATPR.description: PM configuration parameter, related to the L2 low power state. This parameter represents the maximum aggregate transmit power reduction (in dB) that can be performed through a single Power Trim in the L2 state.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2Rate.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2Rate
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2Rate.description: PM configuration parameter, related to the L2 low power state. This parameter specifies the minimum net data rate during the low power state (L2). The data rate is coded in bit/s.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnAtucConfMinINP.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnAtucConfMinINP
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnAtucConfMinINP.description: Parameter used to specify the minimum impulse noise protection for the downstream bearer channel.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2EntryThresh.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2EntryThresholdRate
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2EntryThresh.description: PM configuration parameter, related to the L2 low power state. This parameter specifies the downstream data rate threshold that triggers autonomous entry into low power state (L2). The data rate is coded in bit/s, and must be less than or equal to the value of GSMIB_adslAtucConfGsPML2Exit ThresholdRate.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2ExitThresho.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2ExitThresholdRate
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2ExitThresho.description: PM configuration parameter, related to the L2 low power state. This parameter specifies the downstream data rate threshold that triggers autonomous exit from low power state (L2). The data rate is coded in bit/s, and must be less than the value of GSMIB_adslAtucConfPML2MinRate.

dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2EntryRateMi.name: dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2EntryRateMinTime
dsAdslLineConfProfileExtnPML2EntryRateMi.description: PM configuration parameter, related to the L2 low power state. This parameter specifies the minimum interval of time that the net data rate for the bearer channel should stay below GSMIB_adslAtucConfGsPML2EntryThresholdRate before autonomous entry into low power state (L2). The minimum entry rate time is coded in seconds, and can range from 900 to 65535.

dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileExtnTable.name: dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileExtnTable
dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileExtnTable.description: This table contains information on the ADSL line configuration. This table is an extention to adslLineAlarmConfProfileExtnTable defined in rfc 2662.

dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileExtnEntry.name: dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileExtnEntry
dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileExtnEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileExtnTable. The Table is indexed by adslLineAlarmConfProfileName.

dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileName.name: dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileName
dsAdslLineAlarmConfProfileName.description: This object is used by the line alarm configuration Extn table in order to identify a row of this table. When `dynamic' profiles are implemented, the profile name is user specified. Also, the system will always provide a default profile whose name is `DEND

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinFailFa.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinFailFastR
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinFailFa.description: The number of failed retrains encountered by an ADSL interface within any giving 15 minutes performance data collection period, which cause the SNMP agent to send an adslAtucFailedFastRTrap.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinSesL.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinSesL
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinSesL.description: The number of Severe errored seconds encountered by an ADSL interface within any giving 15 minutes performance data collection period, which cause the SNMP to send an adslAtucSesLTrap.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinUasL.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinUasL
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinUasL.description: The first time the value of the corresponding instance of adslAtucPerf15MinUasL reaches or exceeds this value within a given 15-minute performance data collection period, an adslAtucUasLThreshTrap notifications will be generated.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinFecsL.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinFecsL
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh15MinFecsL.description: The number of Forward error correction seconds encountered by an ADSL interface within any giving 15 Minutes performance data collection period, which cause the SNMP agent to send an ' dsAdslAtucTrapsPerfFecsLThresh'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLofs.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLofs
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLofs.description: The number of Loss of Frame Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAtucPerfLofsThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLoss.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLoss
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLoss.description: The number of Loss of Signal Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAtucPerfLossThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLols.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLols
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLols.description: The number of Loss of Link Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAtucPerfLolsThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLprs.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLprs
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayLprs.description: The number of Loss of Power Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAtucPerfLprsThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayESs.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayESs
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayESs.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAtucPerfESsThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DaySesL.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DaySesL
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DaySesL.description: The number of Severe errored Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAtucPerfSesLThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayUasL.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayUasL
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayUasL.description: The number of unavailable errored seconds encountered by an ADSL interface within any giving 1 day performance data collection period, which cause the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAtucPerfUasLThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayFecsL.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayFecsL
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAtucThresh1DayFecsL.description: The number of Forward error correction seconds encountered by an ADSL interface within any giving 1 day performance data collection period, which cause the SNMP agent to send an ' dsAdslAtucTrapsPerfFecsLThresh1Day'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh15MinFecsL.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh15MinFecsL
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh15MinFecsL.description: The number of Forward error correction seconds encountered by an ADSL interface within any giving 15 Minutes performance data collection period, which cause the SNMP agent to send an ' dsAdslAturTrapsPerfFecsLThresh'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayLofs.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayLofs
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayLofs.description: The number of Loss of Frame Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAturPerfLofsThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayLoss.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayLoss
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayLoss.description: The number of Loss of Signal Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAturPerfLossThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayLprs.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayLprs
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayLprs.description: The number of Loss of Power Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAturPerfLprsThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayESs.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayESs
dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DayESs.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by an ADSL interface, within any given 1 day performance data collection period, which causes the SNMP agent to send an 'dsAdslAturPerfESsThresh1DayTrap'.

dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DaySesL.name: dsAdslLineAlarmExtnAturThresh1DaySesL
